1) DUNE configuration:
     in order to use DUNE 2.3.1  add the following lines to ~/.bashrc

     DUNE_DIR=/usr/local_machine/dune-2.3.1; export DUNE_DIR
     DUNE_SUFFIX=-2.3.1; export DUNE_SUFFIX
     MYDUNEMODULES_DIR=$HOME/my_modules_path; export MYDUNEMODULES_DIR
     source $DUNE_DIR/envar

     where my_modules_path is the folder where the new module of dune will be created.

2) Creation of a new DUNE module:
     in order to create a new DUNE module run the following commands

     createdunemodule module_name

     and follow the instructions.

3) Compilation of a DUNE module:
     in order to compile a DUNE module run the following commands

     compiledunemodule module_name

4) Sumbit a job in cluster:
     in order to compile and run a DUNE code in the cluster run the following commands

     cd $MYDUNEMODULES_DIR/module_name/src
     make clean
     make all
     qsubb module_name output_name [node_number](01 default)

     the output will be saved in /scratchcompXX/user_name/output_name/ where XX is the node_number chosen.

For further information please contact me at m.agnese13@imperial.ac.uk.
